<div id="works">
<h2>Works</h2>
<p><b>Hindustan Socialist Republican Association</b> - He was a key leader in reorganizing the HSRA, aiming for an independent socialist India.</p>
<p><b>Assembly Bombing</b> - He and Batukeshwar Dutt threw non-lethal bombs in the Central Legislative Assembly to protest repressive laws, famously shouting "Inquilab Zindabad."</p>
<p><b>Revolutionary Literature</b> - A prolific writer, he penned the famous essay "Why I am an Atheist" while in prison, showcasing his intellectual depth and socialist vision.</p>
</div>

<div id="legacy">
<h2>Legacy</h2>
<p>Bhagat Singh's bravery and intellectual clarity made him a folk hero in India, inspiring generations of youth to stand up against injustice and tyranny.</p>
